subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Keyboard Layouts
msgSnippet: ... Fair nuff. I don t want to maintain umpteen*2 semi-QWERTY layouts ù two should be enough.
messageBody:
On May 20, 2014, at 8:01 AM, John Cowan cowan@... [Read_Alphabet] <Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com> wrote:

> mailinglists@... [Read_Alphabet] scripsit:
>
> > Thing is, I don't want to maintain umpteen semi-QWERTY layouts —
> > one should be enough.
>
> I'm a keyboard maintainer too, but there really is no alternative to
> supporting both US and UK keyboard layouts.

Fair 'nuff. I don't want to maintain umpteen*2 semi-QWERTY layouts — two should be enough.
